| `go test ./...` | Run all tests |

## Architecture

This project uses **Go + Gin** web framework:

- **cmd/server/main.go** — Application entrypoint
- **internal/server/server.go** — Gin server setup with routes
- **internal/server/handlers.go** — Route handlers (CRUD)
- **internal/server/server_test.go** — Handler tests with httptest

Key conventions:

- Clean architecture with internal package encapsulation
- `New()` factory creates `*http.Server` for testability
- `Run()` adds graceful shutdown for production
- In-memory store (swappable for PostgreSQL via pgx)
- Standard `{ success, data, error }` JSON response shape
